        "content": "<p>Hi, everyone! I'm new here. I'm considering supporting τ = 2π = 6.28318... in Mathlib.<br>\nAs you may know, τ, defined to be the ratio of a circle’s circumference (length) to its radius, has been advocated for 15 years to be the \"true circle constant\", according to <a href=\"https://www.tauday.com/tau-manifesto\">https://www.tauday.com/tau-manifesto</a>. However, it seems that τ is still not supported in Mathlib.<br>\nTo support τ, we'll introduce <code>Real.tau</code>, and have <code>Mathlib.Data.Real.Tau.Irrational</code> to prove that τ is irrational, etc.<br>\nI still have little knowledge about Lean, and I consider contributing τ as a chance to learn more about the Mathlib. Is there someone interested in this topic? Any suggestions? Glad to hear from you!</p>",
        "id": 536982495,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
        "timestamp": 1756646180
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think we need this</p>",
        "id": 536982627,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756646276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>why can't we just use <code>2 * π</code> everywhere</p>",
        "id": 536982645,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756646294
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for the same reason we do <code>exp 1</code> instead of defining <code>Real.e</code></p>",
        "id": 536982763,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756646403
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Because, π is 1/2 τ, not that τ is 2 * π</p>",
        "id": 536982836,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
        "timestamp": 1756646484
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>τists will find it comfortable to write without π.</p>",
        "id": 536982882,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
        "timestamp": 1756646525
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well in mathlib <code>π</code> is defined as \"twice an arbitrary zero of <code>Real.cos</code> between <code>1</code> and <code>2</code>, which exists by the intermediate value theorem\"</p>",
        "id": 536982916,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756646559
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's interesting.</p>",
        "id": 536982980,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
        "timestamp": 1756646638
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Then how is <code>Real.cos</code> defined, if I may know?</p>",
        "id": 536983049,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
        "timestamp": 1756646704
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>anything can be defined in multiple ways and it doesn't really matter which one you pick as long as it's easy to work with and you can prove all the properties</p>",
        "id": 536983059,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756646708
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My long-term experience has told me that it is always more meaningful and more concise to write in τ, however.</p>",
        "id": 536983139,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
        "timestamp": 1756646784
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"939943\">Xuanmizhen</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Support.20.CF.84.20.28tau.29.20as.20the.20circle.20constant.20in.20Mathlib.3F/near/536983049\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Then how is <code>Real.cos</code> defined, if I may know?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><code>Real.cos</code> is \"the real part of <code>Complex.cos</code>\", and <code>Complex.cos</code> is defined as <code>z ↦ (exp (z * I) + exp (-z * I)) / 2</code>, and <code>Complex.exp</code> is defined by its taylor series at zero</p>",
        "id": 536983168,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756646822
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I don't know Complex has cos before.</p>",
        "id": 536983253,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
        "timestamp": 1756646895
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I will learn what you told me further in the future. Anyway, I still believe my intuition, and one day I will write more elegant definitions with tau in the Mathlib, if I could.</p>",
        "id": 536983325,
        "sender_full_name": "Xuanmizhen",
