    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"321459\">Damiano Testa</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Support.20.CF.84.20.28tau.29.20as.20the.20circle.20constant.20in.20Mathlib.3F/near/537090156\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Does that also look inside proofs?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Indeed, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddChar.zmod_injective#doc\">docs#AddChar.zmod_injective</a> does not appear if you search for both, but <code>AddChar.zmod_injective</code> uses <code>Real.pi</code> in its proof.</p>",
